3. MANDATORY DOWNSTREAM DISCLOSURE RIDER

As an express condition of the rights granted under this license, any individual, group, or organization that creates, publishes, deploys, or utilizes a Derivative Work MUST publicly disclose the existence of their derivation and make it known to the Parent Project.

A. Timeline for Disclosure:
The disclosure must be completed within thirty (30) days of the first public release, public deployment, or active distribution of the Derivative Work.

B. Method of Notification:
The notification must be submitted to the Parent Project by doing at least one of the following:
1. Opening a public issue on the Parent Project's official repository (https://github.com/dev-centr/prohelp) containing the disclosure information.
2. Submitting a pull request to include the Derivative Work in the Parent Project's official registry or documentation.

C. Required Disclosure Information:
The notification must include:
1. The official name of the Derivative Work.
2. A direct, publicly accessible link to the source code repository of the Derivative Work.
3. A brief description of the modifications, ports, or extensions made to the Parent Project's Software.


